ms who are neighbors, friends, and kin? Between Muslims provides an ethnographic account of Iraqi Kurdish Muslims who turn away from devotional piety yet remain intimately engaged with Islamic traditions and with other Muslims. Andrew Bush offers a new way to understand religious difference in Islam, rejecting simple stereotypes about ethnic or sectarian identities. Integrating textual analysis of poetry, sermons, and Islamic history into accounts of everyday life in Iraqi Kurdistan, Between Muslims illuminates the interplay of attraction and aversion to Islam among ordinary Muslims.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIrreligionzIraqzKurdistān. 0aIrreligionzIraqzKurdistān. 0aIslamzIraqzKurdistānxCustoms and practices. 0aIslamzIraqzKurdistānxCustoms and practices. 0aIslamic ethicszIraqzKurdistān. 0aIslamic ethicszIraqzKurdistān. 0aKurdszIraqzKurdistānxReligion. 0aKurdszIraqzKurdistānxReligion. 0aMuslimsxReligious lifezIraqzKurdistān. 0aMuslimsxReligious lifezIraqzKurdistān. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Islamic Studies.2bisacsh  aEthics.  aEthnography.  aGender and Family.  aIraq.  aIslam.  aIslamism.  aKurdistan.  aPoetry.  aSufism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361459840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503614598423Coveruhttps: